displayProperties.name: A Rising Chorus: Act I
displayProperties.description:
Failsafe has detected an energy signature on Nessus matching that of NES002. She has dubbed it NES002-C and requests your on-the-ground assistance with hunting it down. She's excited to try out her new proximity sensor.

Complete a run of Breach Executable and locate NES002-C.

displayProperties.name: Planetary Piston Hammer
displayProperties.description:
A specially crafted hammer capable of activating one of the Planetary Pistons on Nessus. Watch your toes.

The hammer will regenerate charges as you complete Echo activities throughout the system. If totally exhausted, it will regenerate one charge daily.

displayProperties.name: Standard Research Bay
displayProperties.description: An empty research bay where Failsafe can store specimens.

displayProperties.name: Seized Radiolite Incubator
displayProperties.description: NES001: An incubator used to reform resistant radiolaria into new physical structures.

displayProperties.name: Encoded Log
displayProperties.description:
Explore Nessus to find the source of a reported VexNet integration on the planetoid.

Hidden Agents have informed you of an interesting lead near the Well of Echoes.

displayProperties.name: Encoded Log
displayProperties.description: Find and complete the Enigma Protocol activity.

displayProperties.name: Assimilated Beacon
displayProperties.description: A signal beacon was dropped from one of the high-value targets in the Echoes Battlegrounds. It appears to emit a powerful signal, which matches readings reported to originate from somewhere in Watcher's Grave on Nessus.

displayProperties.name: Standard Radiolite Sampler
displayProperties.description:
A special tool used for collecting and storing Radiolite samples. Allows you to collect these types of Radiolite samples from Episode: Echoes activities:

 Iridescent
 Ivory
 Crimson

Due to Iridescent Radiolite's unstable nature, it has a tendency to denature into simpler forms of Radiolite during the sampling process.

Storage capacity: {var:2152577323}g

displayProperties.name: Primary Engram Focusing
displayProperties.description:
Unlocks focusing of Echo Engrams into the following Echo gear once added to your collection:

Weapons:
 Ill Omen
 Lost Signal
 Faith-Keeper
 Timeworn Wayfarer
 Veiled Threat
 Sightline Survey

All Echo armor

-Inserted comment: I think I've got this focusing thing down, Captain. Only a 0.3% chance of engram deletion!

displayProperties.name: Specimen ID: NES001
displayProperties.description: Speak with Failsafe in the H.E.L.M. to review her final specimen analysis report.

displayProperties.name: Specimen ID: NES001
displayProperties.description:
Failsafe has found that the incubator specimen contains remnants of both radiolite and base radiolaria. She requires more ambient data from interactions with Vex.

Secure Extracted Data for Failsafe in the Breach Executable activity, which can be launched from the H.E.L.M.

Higher-difficulty completions grant faster progress.

displayProperties.name: Specimen ID: NES001
displayProperties.description: Failsafe has fabricated a Piston Hammer for you. Striking Vex Assimilation Pistons with it will drive nearby veins of Radiolite to the surface for sampling.
